  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@DusanDragulaGR @louisfisch  Did you find a workaround? \nOr is there any update on the issue? @Haroenv \n\nWe ended up doing this:\n```typescript\n<div suppressHydrationWarning={true}>\n\t{!isClient && (\n\t\t<InstantSearchNext\n\t\t\tsearchClient={searchClient}\n\t\t\tindexName={index}>\n\t\t</InstantSearchNext>\n\t)}\n\n\n\t{isClient && (\n\t\t<InstantSearch\n\t\t\tsearchClient={searchClient}\n\t\t\tindexName={index}\n\t\t\t}>\n\t\t\t{Children}\n\t\t</InstantSearch>\n\t)}\n</div>\n```\n\nBut this solution has the drawback that the index is hit twice. Additionally, the CLS (cumulativ layout shift) is increased.",
